Quote:  <i>Tangi, holding a.</i> Faced with a problem or a set-back: New Zealand: C. 20. B., 1941. Ex Maori tangi, `a wake'. Cf. prec. entry.
Notes:

Date:  28/10/1893
Source:  Observer (Auckland)
Author:
Vol / Page:  22
Edition:
Quote:  I hear that Miss Lelia Williams, who was pronounced by the verdict of those present as being the belle, in view of the feeling displayed by some of the disappointed ones, does not intend to accept the kind offer of Mr Foy, of having her photo enlarged, but intends instead to hold a tangi at Kopu over the remains of 'blighted hopes' of those who thought they were entitled to the coverted [sic] honour, and for the occasion she purposes [sic] wearing the same costume, so that even the Maoris will not think she is anything but a princess of their own blood, as the majority of those present at the ball did.
Notes:

